projects.project_description: This project focuses on understanding the concepts of Spectral Graph Theory, the math behind it and applying it to the diverse field of networks and topology.  Partitioning helps in decomposing complex systems into submodules which allows the manufacturer to develop and integrate different modules independently. Here, we implement spectral clustering to split an image into its main components.
The project aims to classify a given piece of news as real or fake. The model is trained using Natural Language Processing on a dataset of real and fake news ,which is used to predict the result.

Developing a Real-time kernel for ARM-Cortex M series processors which involves developing a scheduler and other operating system entities like synchronization primitives to provide a concurrent execution environment for processes
An all-terrain vehicle with an adaptive suspension that is capable of climbing obstacles (walls).(https://github.com/spider-tronix/shadow-bot)
Design and control of a wheel capable of varying its radius over a range of values using a novel transformation mechanism.

Braille is a system of raised dots that help the visually impaired people to read. Unfortunately, the number of text material available in Braille is critically low and costly to manufacture and maintain. With around 12 million blind people, India is a home to the world's largest number of blind people. Existing products like the refreshable Braille displays cost around $10,000 making it almost impossible for a common blind person in India to afford(especially for children in blind schools). This project aims at developing an affordable and a portable braille reader which can translate printed text material instantly into braille for the visually impaired to read.

A robotic system based on two emerging fields of technology: SWARM ROBOTICS and BLOCKCHAIN. The research paper was accepted at The 6th International Conference on Control, Automation and Robotics ( IEEE ICCAR 2020 ) to be held during April 20-23, 2020 (Singapore)
A document scanner for effective document capturing and storage. Allows user to share files in multiple formats and has features to improve document quality. Project can replace CamScanner.

An app to keep in touch with the alumni of REC/NITT in the Middle East. The app allows alumni to connect and network with other alumni, build new connections, do social and professional networking, interact with mentors, get employment support and volunteer for events

Orientation App is all about the events and affairs that will ease a fresher’s way into NIT Trichy. The prominent features of the app include timeline of all the events, live event streaming, map of the main hotspots of the campus, push notifications, contact details of the Orientation team and peer supporters of all the departments. It also has vital information regarding the programme itself, guidelines to have a safe stay in campus and so much more.
Admin Portal for the Alumni Association UAE Chapter. Handles data updation, deletion and provides analytics on the data of RecalUAE.

The system aims to provide an easy experience for students to request approval on certificates. A unified portal allows both students and administrators to log in using institute credentials to either send or approve requests. The portal handles all the required student information, forms, and receipts to make the process as streamlined as possible for administrators. Functionality is provided for administrators to approve/reject requests in a single click and view student information and required documents on a single interface.

Happy Hunt Challenge is a PWA React Application built for a Scavenger Hunt game conducted by Event Specials in Pune. The app has 1500+ users who need to solve missions (clues) scattered all over Pune. The website has two portals, one for the Admin and another for end-users. The admin portal has features like auto evaluation, admin evaluation, adding or updating the missions, feed control, etc. The end-user interface consists of a portal to check clues and submit answers to the clues after reaching a particular location. If their submissions are accepted, then the players are awarded points, and their submissions get auto-posted in the feed, where other players can react to it by liking or sharing. The project uses the MERN stack.

 • Designed a vehicle data extraction pipeline from the ground up, using a FasterRCNN implementation with Resnet101 for vehicle data extraction
• Working on implementing a frontend and backend to relay data between the camera and the system.

The Homebrew Bionics is a community that explores the possibilities of developing open-source, affordable prosthetic devices that are rapidly fabricable. If you are someone who would love to contribute, kindly visit https://homebrew-bionics.github.io/.

UHUGV is an amphibious bot that is capable of traversing both land and underwater. The ground locomotion is achieved by track drive and the underwater motion is achieved by bio-mimicking fin ray fish locomotion. The robot has a track drive mechanism for the purpose of traveling in marshy terrains. It has 4 servo motors on either side of the robot to enable its movement underwater by implementing the mathematical model of fin ray motion. We can control the movement of the bot underwater by adjusting the amplitude and angular frequency of the servos attached to a fin-like material. This bot can be used as a recon to gain insights without being spotted. The onboard controller is capable of sending real-time data acquired to the command center through WiFi using a WiFi-module.

Beebots is a swarm robotics project that aims to explore swarm intelligence and coordination using biologically inspired algorithms with a focus on shape formation and recovery from obstacles and disturbances.

OTA (Over the Air) Programming is a process which allows devices to upgrade their firmware or software wirelessly without any physical access. The project aims in developing a universal module having OTA functionality for AVR microcontrollers without any built in Wifi support.

This project aims at developing an RTL design of a microprocessor core that can Support the RISC V instruction set Architecture. The core would be further optimized for different applications and made completely open-sourced for anyone to use.

projects.project_name: DarkSight: Extreme Low-Light Image Processing Pipeline
projects.project_description: DarkSight attains extreme low light image enhancement by combining video feed inputs from a regular camera and a thermal camera. This is performed using Computer Vision by learning to map the low exposure images to high exposure images using an architecture known as a UNet. Check out the source code and slides here: https://github.com/spider-tronix/Dark-Sight
Multi-agent assistive system : A cooperative system consisting of a UAV assisting an UGV.
Crawlocator is a remotely controlled amphibious hexapod(six legged) that can travel into a disaster zone, locate victims and transmit their location back.

Our project strives to bridge the gap and enable effortless communication between users of conventional language and sign language by utilizing cost effective mini-potentiometric pots in our gloves with 3D printed parts to detect finger movements. The gloves are paired with a smartphone to perform sign translation using machine learning and natural language processing to produce audio and visual output.
A GPR assisted landmine detection bot that uses DL pipeline, continuous track and arm mechanism for probing and demining.
